text.section:
This section shall not be construed as:
Prohibiting an employer from requiring that an employee inform him or her of an official request made to an agency for information, or the substance of testimony made, or to be made, by the employee to legislators on behalf of an agency;
Permitting the employee to leave his or her assigned work area during normal work hours without following applicable law, administrative regulations, rules, or policies pertaining to leave, unless the employee is requested by the Kentucky Legislative Ethics Commission or the Executive Branch Ethics Commission to appear before the commission, or by a legislator or a legislative committee to appear before a legislative committee;
Authorizing an employee to represent his or her personal opinions as the opinions of his or her employer; or
Prohibiting disciplinary or punitive action if an employee discloses information which he or she knows:
To be false or which he or she discloses with reckless disregard for its truth or falsity;
To be exempt from required disclosure under the provisions of KRS 61.870 to 61.884; or
Is confidential under any other provision of law.
